<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1321,2038]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,296,1392,1418]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Note:—</emphasis>
Three species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hooker &amp; Arnott" authorityYear="1834" box="[518,615,1393,1418]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Tweedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[518,615,1393,1418]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Tweedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hooker, W. J. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W." box="[824,1137,1393,1419]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" pagination="276 - 296" refId="ref5089" refString="Hooker, W. J. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W. (1834) Contributions towards a flora of South America and the islands of the Pacific. 1. Extra-tropical South America. Journal of Botany, being a second series of the Botanical Miscellany 1: 276 - 296" type="journal article" year="1834">Hooker &amp; Arnott (1834)</bibRefCitation>
, and each of these has subsequently been designated by different authors as the 
<typeStatus box="[852,963,1432,1458]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">lectotype</typeStatus>
of the genus. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Malme, G. O. A." box="[1261,1436,1432,1458]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref5554" refString="Malme, G. O. A. (1904) Uber die Asclepiadaceen-Gattun Tweedia Hooker &amp; Arnott. Arkiv for Botanik utgivet av Kongliga Svenska Vetenskapsakademien 2 (7): 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1904">Malme (1904)</bibRefCitation>
revised the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hooker &amp; Arnott" authorityYear="1834" box="[360,459,1471,1496]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Tweedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[360,459,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Tweedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and emended its concept, he did not indicate a type. The first to do so was T. 
<bibRefCitation author="Meyer, T." pageId="4" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 121" refId="ref5889" refString="Meyer, T. (1944) Asclepiadaceae. In: Descole, H. R. (Ed), Genera et Species Plantarum Argentinarum, vol. 2. Guillermo Kraft, Buenos Aires, 1 - 273, tab. 1 - 121." type="book chapter" year="1944">Meyer (1944: 102)</bibRefCitation>
, who chose 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hooker &amp; Arnott" authorityYear="1834" box="[464,609,1509,1534]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Tweedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brunonis">
<emphasis box="[464,609,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">T. brunonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as his “especie genérica” for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hooker &amp; Arnott" authorityYear="1834" box="[999,1103,1509,1534]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Tweedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[999,1103,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Tweedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hooker, W. J. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W." box="[1122,1436,1509,1535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" pagination="276 - 296" refId="ref5089" refString="Hooker, W. J. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W. (1834) Contributions towards a flora of South America and the islands of the Pacific. 1. Extra-tropical South America. Journal of Botany, being a second series of the Botanical Miscellany 1: 276 - 296" type="journal article" year="1834">Hooker &amp; Arnott (1834)</bibRefCitation>
questioned the future generic placement of this species when they erected the genus and described the species. They listed two characters for the genus: the form of the corona, and the bifid style-head appendage. As their description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hooker &amp; Arnott" authorityYear="1834" box="[321,455,1625,1650]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Tweedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brunonis">
<emphasis box="[321,455,1625,1650]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">T. brunonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
notes the stigma to be undivided, a “serious conflict” with the protologue could be argued, leading to a rejection of Meyer´s lectotypification under Art. 9.17 of the Code. But the apex of the style-head appendage is, in fact, shortly bilobed, as shown by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rua, G. H." box="[877,1013,1702,1728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" pagination="375 - 410" refId="ref6235" refString="Rua, G. H. (1989). Revision taxonomica del genero Tweedia (Asclepiadaceae). Parodiana 5: 375 - 410." type="journal article" year="1989">Rua (1989)</bibRefCitation>
. Nomenclaturally, Hooker &amp; Arnott made the combination under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hooker &amp; Arnott" authorityYear="1834" box="[505,604,1741,1766]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Tweedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[505,604,1741,1766]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Tweedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the taxonomic opinion expressed subsequently does not negate this.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1321,2038]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">
<bibRefCitation author="Bullock, A. A." box="[198,425,1818,1844]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" pagination="97 - 100" refId="ref4494" refString="Bullock, A. A. (1958) Nomenclatural notes: VI. Kew Bulletin 13: 97 - 100." type="journal article" year="1958">Bullock (1958: 99)</bibRefCitation>
was presumably unaware of Meyer’s typification when he designated 
<taxonomicName authority="Hooker &amp; Arnott (1834: 291)" authorityName="Hooker &amp; Arnott" authorityPageNumber="291" authorityYear="1834" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Tweedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrolepis">
<emphasis box="[1276,1436,1819,1844]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">T. macrolepis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hooker, W. J. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W." box="[151,495,1857,1883]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" pagination="276 - 296" refId="ref5089" refString="Hooker, W. J. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W. (1834) Contributions towards a flora of South America and the islands of the Pacific. 1. Extra-tropical South America. Journal of Botany, being a second series of the Botanical Miscellany 1: 276 - 296" type="journal article" year="1834">Hooker &amp; Arnott (1834: 291)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus box="[534,584,1857,1883]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
of the genus. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rua, G. H." box="[748,880,1857,1883]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" pagination="375 - 410" refId="ref6235" refString="Rua, G. H. (1989). Revision taxonomica del genero Tweedia (Asclepiadaceae). Parodiana 5: 375 - 410." type="journal article" year="1989">Rua (1989)</bibRefCitation>
argued that Bullock's designation was arbitrary and therefore contrary to the code (although this does not stand up to scrutiny, and was a superfluous designation in any case). Rua selected 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hooker &amp; Arnott 1830: 35) Hooker &amp; Arnott (1834: 291)" authorityName="Hooker &amp; Arnott" authorityPageNumber="291" authorityYear="1834" baseAuthorityName="Hooker &amp; Arnott" baseAuthorityPageNumber="35" baseAuthorityYear="1830" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Tweedia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="birostrata">
<emphasis box="[625,776,1935,1960]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">T. birostrata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hooker, W. J. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W." box="[793,1121,1934,1960]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" refId="ref5016" refString="Hooker, W. J. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W. (1830) The Botany of Captain Beechey's Voyage Comprising an Account of the Plants Collected by Messrs. Ley and Collie, and other Officers of the Expedition, During the Voyage to the Pacific and Bering's Strait, Performed in His Majesty's ship Blo. H. G. Bohn, London, 485 pp." type="book" year="1830">Hooker &amp; Arnott 1830: 35</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Hooker, W. J. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W." pageId="4" pageNumber="13" pagination="276 - 296" refId="ref5089" refString="Hooker, W. J. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W. (1834) Contributions towards a flora of South America and the islands of the Pacific. 1. Extra-tropical South America. Journal of Botany, being a second series of the Botanical Miscellany 1: 276 - 296" type="journal article" year="1834">Hooker &amp; Arnott (1834: 291)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which 
<bibRefCitation author="Ezcurra, C." box="[301,526,1973,1999]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" pagination="58 - 77" refId="ref4663" refString="Ezcurra, C. (1999) Asclepiadaceae. In: Correa, M. N. (ed.), Flora Patagonica VI. Instituto Nacional de Technologia Agropecuaria, Buenos Aires, pp. 58 - 77." type="book chapter" year="1999">Ezcurra (1999: 75)</bibRefCitation>
then followed in Flora Patagonica. The earliest designation is that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Meyer, T." pageId="4" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 121" refId="ref5889" refString="Meyer, T. (1944) Asclepiadaceae. In: Descole, H. R. (Ed), Genera et Species Plantarum Argentinarum, vol. 2. Guillermo Kraft, Buenos Aires, 1 - 273, tab. 1 - 121." type="book chapter" year="1944">Meyer (1944)</bibRefCitation>
and must be adopted.
</paragraph>
